# start Validation Reply Form
_vrf_PLAT342_dbr-pea_twin1_hklf5 
;
PROBLEM: Low Bond Precision on C-C Bonds ............... 0.03 Ang.
RESPONSE: The crystal was twinned, and the twinning could 
only be partly resolved.  The twinning, strong  scatterers 
(Pb, I and Br) and strong absorption contributed to the low 
precision of the lighter scatterers.
;
# end Validation Reply Form
